Introduction

TFN (Korean: 티에프앤; Japanese: ティエフアン; formerly known as T1419) is a nine-member boy group under MLD Entertainment. They made their debut on January 11, 2021 with their first single album "Before Sunrise Part. 1".

On October 13, 2020 MLD Entertainment announced they would be launching a new boy group in December in partnership with NHN and Sony Music. The group would debut not only in Korea but also in Japan and the United States, simultaneously. It was also announced that MLD had signed a business partner agreement with ICM Partners for activities in the U.S.

On October 17, 2022 MLD rebranded the group's name to TFN and added the meaning of "Try For New" to the existing "Teenager Fourteen Nineteen".

According to media outlet reports on February 29 KST, boy group TFN, under MLD Entertainment, has disbanded as of February 2024. After choosing to end their group activities, members Leo, Zero, Kairi, and Kio have returned to their homes in Japan.
